This tgz includes 2 files

    dstar-regcheck
    dstar-regcheck.pl

The first is a shell script. This should be copied to the cgi-bin directory of your web server.
The second is a perl-script which I placed in /usr/local/bin. 
This will be started from the shell-script with the callsign entered by the user.
The language of the output is switched by the locale-setting of the browser.
Currently only "DE" is emplemented for German, all other settings will switch to English language.

The tool needs to have access to a D-Star gateway's database.
By default postgres is configured to only listen on 127.0.0.1.
If you want to run the tool on a different server you will need to change that in postgres.conf or use a tunnel.
Please be careful when opening the database to the internet!

Take care to change the header, footer and URLs to your need.

